---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon" description="How this site is built.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Colophon</h1>
    <p>
      This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>,
      styled with <a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a>,
      and deployed on <a href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Content is written in Markdown/MDX and managed through
      <a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/content-collections/">Astro Content Collections</a>.
      The type system is enforced with TypeScript and Zod schemas.
    </p>
    <p>
      Typography is set in <a href="https://rsms.me/inter/">Inter</a> for body text
      and <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/lp/mono/">JetBrains Mono</a> for code.
    </p>
    <p>
      The design philosophy: minimal, fast, content-first. No tracking scripts,
      no cookie banners, no JavaScript frameworks loading megabytes of code to
      render text on a screen.
    </p>
    <p>
      The source code is available on <a href="https://github.com/parkerferguson/parkerferguson-dot-xyz">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
